# Description
This repository emulates a microservice with multiple endpoints that will work as an image classifier and tagging based on image recognition from IMAGGA.

We will use ImageKit for storage, MySQL as database and Flask to run the app.

The enpoints available are:
````
POST {localhost_url}/images

body = {'image': <image_base_64>}

# Example of response
{'data': '',
 'date': '2024-05-29 18:52:53',
 'id': '2325688d-fde6-4bff-96d0-ecda5fd7ed8b',
 'size': 117.3359375,
 'tags': [{'confidence': 100, 'tag': 'bottle'},
  {'confidence': 95.1903381347656, 'tag': 'lager'}]}
````

# Setup
## Installation
- Clone this repository to your local computer
- Ensure you have docker installed and running
- Navigate to /src/ folder of the repository
## Credentials
- In your /src/ folder, create a ```credentials.json``` file with the following structure:
````
{
    "IMAGEKIT_PUBLIC_KEY" : <your_key>,
    "IMAGEKIT_PRIVATE_KEY" : <your_key>,
    "IMAGGA_API_KEY" : <your_key>,
    "IMAGGA_API_SECRET" : <your_key>
}
````
*Note: to obtain your API keys, refer to IMAGEKIT and IMAGGA documentation*
## Execution
The following instructions must be done in your /src/ folder.
- Run ```docker-compose build```
- Run ```docker-compose up```
- Open ```Microservicios.ipynb```
- Navigate to ```Solucin``` and start executing the cells, you can call the API using whatever method you prefer on your local computer
